A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class-action lawsuit against the company.
The lawsuit involves allegations of fraud and corporate looting by former directors and officers.
Former executives Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz are accused of stealing over $600 million from Tyco.
Prosecutors claim they hid unauthorized bonuses and inflated stock prices.
The retrial focuses on their lavish spending and deception.
Defense lawyers argue they earned their compensation legitimately.
The trial highlights the consequences of corporate scandals on workers, clients, and investors.
Prosecutors are emphasizing the illegal actions of the executives in awarding themselves bonuses and concealing them.
